# Styling Conventions

## Colors & Theming (Dark Mode Aware)

Always use `Theme.of(context)` to resolve colors. **Never** use raw `Color(0x...)`, `Colors.white`, or `Colors.black` directly in UI widgets. Do not call `AppColors` directly from UI widgets, as it bypasses the theme engine.

```dart
// ✅ GOOD
color: Theme.of(context).colorScheme.primary,
color: Theme.of(context).colorScheme.onSurface,
color: Theme.of(context).cardColor,

// ❌ BAD
color: AppColors.primaryColor // Inflexible for theme changes
color: Colors.white // Breaks dark mode backgrounds
color: Colors.black // Breaks dark mode text
color: Color(0xFF023E8A) // Hardcoded colors
```

**Common semantic mappings:**
- **Backgrounds:** `Theme.of(context).scaffoldBackgroundColor`
- **Cards / Containers:** `Theme.of(context).cardColor`
- **App/Title Text:** `Theme.of(context).colorScheme.onSurface` (Never `Colors.black`)
- **Hint Text / Subtitles:** `Theme.of(context).hintColor`
- **Primary Actions:** `Theme.of(context).colorScheme.primary` (Text inside: `colorScheme.onPrimary` or `Colors.white`)
- **Action Buttons Background fading:** Use `Theme.of(context).colorScheme.primary.withOpacity(0.1)` instead of hardcoded pastel generic colors.

**Important Note on `const`**: When injecting `Theme.of(context)` into a widget tree, remove `const` from parents that wrap the `Theme` call (e.g. `const BoxDecoration` -> `BoxDecoration`).

## Typography — `TextStyles`

All text styles are in `lib/core/utils/app_text_styles.dart`. Always call them with `BuildContext`.

```dart
// ✅ GOOD
Text('Hello', style: TextStyles.semiBold16(context))

// ❌ BAD
Text('Hello', style: TextStyle(fontSize: 16, fontWeight: FontWeight.w600))
```

Available styles (format: `{weight}{size}`):

- `regular11`, `semiBold11`
- `regular12`, `regular13`, `bold13`, `semiBold13`
- `regular14`, `medium14`, `semiBold14`
- `medium15`, `semiBold15`
- `regular16`, `medium16`, `semiBold16`, `bold16`
- `regular18`, `medium18`, `bold18`
- `semiBold19`, `bold19`
- `regular20`, `medium20`, `semiBold20`
- `regular22`, `bold22`, `bold23`
- `semiBold24`, `regular26`, `bold28`

To tint: `.copyWith(color: AppColors.primaryColor)`.

## Sizing — `flutter_screenutil`

Design size is **375×812**. Always use `.w`, `.h`, `.r`, `.sp` — never raw doubles for layout.

```dart
// ✅ GOOD
SizedBox(width: 24.w, height: 8.h)
BorderRadius.circular(12.r)

// ❌ BAD
SizedBox(width: 24, height: 8)
```

## Fonts

| Locale | Font Family |
|--------|-------------|
| `ar` | `Cairo` (400/500/600/700) |
| `en` | `Inter` (400/500/600/700) |

The font family is set globally in `MaterialApp` based on locale. Never override `fontFamily` in individual `TextStyle`.

## Constants

`AppConstants` in `lib/core/utils/app_constants.dart` is a compatibility shim for app config values such as `baseUrl`, `apiKey`, and OAuth IDs. Do not treat it as a styling token source; styling still comes from `AppColors`, `TextStyles`, `ScreenUtil`, and `AppImages`.

## Assets

Images are in `assets/images/` and `assets/images/vuesax/bold|outline/`. Reference via the generated `AppImages` class in `lib/core/utils/app_images.dart`.

SVGs use `flutter_svg`; rasters use standard `Image.asset`.
